<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM AFTERMATH</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28  2:12:31 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
 I was 10 in 1965 and 20 in 1975. My most formative years<br>
were spent watching the War on TV. My father was a WWII<br>
vet. His father fought in WWI and we heard nightly how we<br>
had to do well in school or we'd end up over there.Yet my<br>
father backed the war effort and was against the protesters.<br>
 I guess it was an honorable war but not for his sons. My<br>
oldest brother received a deferment and the next got a high<br>
number and it ended(the draft) before I had my turn. My<br>
father died in 1973. I was disallusioned with both this<br>
country and its leaders. Little has changed for me. I am<br>
in this for myself and family. 
